I need to identify the capital contributed by shareholders in exchange for shares from the balance sheet. This is typically represented by "Paid-in Capital" or similar line items in the Owner's Equity section.

Looking at the provided balance sheet, I can see the "Paid-in Capital" line item which represents the capital contributed by shareholders.

From the balance sheet:
- Initial value of Paid-in Capital: 13000000.00 (as of 2023-12-31)
- End value of Paid-in Capital: 13000000.00 (as of 2024-01-27)

This means the shareholders' capital contribution remained unchanged between the initial and end dates.

```json
{"solution": {'initial value': '13000000.00', 'end value': '13000000.00'}}
```
